{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871208596,"sessionID":"ses_285d5f3a3ffeBQhx48Y79H3M06","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2a1b59001FNsJ9QjNwOIMkx","messageID":"msg_d7a2a0d58001lOiZ1l4LvhzHyc","sessionID":"ses_285d5f3a3ffeBQhx48Y79H3M06","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"toolu_28abd3b370d64ae1a16a9bb6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"Explore agentcube project structure","description":"Explore agentcube project","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project in /home/dsj/benchmark to understand:\n1. Overall project structure and purpose\n2. What kind of project this is (infrastructure, application, etc.)\n3. Existing proposal.md files to understand the format and style\n4. Any Helm-related configurations or manifests\n5. The manifests module structure\n6. Any existing AR (Architecture Record) or ADR documents\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary including:\n- Project overview\n- Directory structure\n- Examples of existing proposal.md format (if any)\n- Any Helm chart configurations found\n- Information about the manifests module","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_285d5d944ffe5F72D5t70TRdlK (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nNow I have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is the summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Summary: AgentCube Project\n\n### 1. Project Overview\n\n**AgentCube** is a **Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents**. It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n**Project Type:** Infrastructure / Cloud-Native Platform (Go + Python)\n\n**Module:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n\n**Key Technologies:**\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24 |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python >= 3.10 |\n| HTTP Framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs, controller-runtime, agent-sandbox |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey |\n| Auth | JWT RS256, K8s TokenReview |\n| Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker |\n\n---\n\n### 2. Directory Structure\n\nThe workspace at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z` contains:\n\n```\nagentcube/              # Python SDK (agentcube package)\n  ├── cli/              # CLI toolkit (Typer)\n  ├── clients/          # HTTP clients (ControlPlane, DataPlane)\n  ├── models/           # Pydantic models\n  ├── operations/       # SDK operations\n  ├── runtime/          # Runtime abstractions\n  ├── services/         # Service layer\n  └── utils/            # Utilities\ncmd/                    # Go binary entry points\n  ├── agentd/           # Idle cleanup controller\n  ├── picod/            # PicoD execution engine\n  ├── router/           # Session-aware HTTP proxy\n  └── workload-manager/ # Workload manager service\npkg/                    # Go packages\n  ├── agentd/           # Agentd controller\n  ├── apis/             # CRD definitions\n  ├── client/           # Generated client-go\n  ├── common/           # Common utilities\n  ├── picod/            # PicoD execution\n  ├── router/           # Router logic\n  ├── store/            # Redis/Valkey store\n  └── workloadmanager/ # Workload manager\nchanges/                # AR (Architecture Records) - AR-001 to AR-030\n  ├── AR-001/ ... AR-030/\n  │   ├── proposal.md   # (some ARs)\n  │   ├── design.md    # Design document\n  │   ├── delta-spec.md # GIVEN/WHEN/THEN acceptance criteria\n  │   └── tasks.md     # Implementation tasks\ndeployment/             # Helm chart design docs\n  ├── design.md        # Full Helm chart design\n  ├── spec.md          # Deployment requirements\n  └── client-go.md     # client-go generation\ntesting/               # Test specifications\n  └── agentcube_tdd_manifest.md  # TDD test contracts\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Proposal.md Format\n\nThe main `proposal.md` at the workspace root (`/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md`) follows this structure:\n\n```markdown\n# AR-XXX: [Title]\n\n## Summary\n[Brief overview]\n\n## Purpose\n### Background\n[Problem statement and context]\n\n### Goal\n[What this AR aims to achieve]\n\n### Value\n[Business/technical value]\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| ... | ... | ... |\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n- Item 1\n- Item 2\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n| Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n|------------|---------|--------|\n| ... | ... | ... |\n\n### Upstream\n- [Document references]\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n1. ...\n2. ...\n\n### Risks\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| ... | ... | ... |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: [Name] (Not Selected)\n**Pros**: ...\n**Cons**: ...\n```\n\nThe changes/AR-XXX/ directories use a variant with:\n- `proposal.md` - High-level proposal (when present)\n- `design.md` - Detailed design\n- `delta-spec.md` - GIVEN/WHEN/THEN acceptance scenarios\n- `tasks.md` - Implementation task breakdown\n\n---\n\n### 4. Helm Chart Configurations\n\nFound in `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/deployment/`:\n\n**Design Document:** `deployment/design.md` contains complete Helm chart specification:\n\n- **Chart.yaml**: `name: agentcube`, `version: 0.1.0`, `appVersion: 1.0.0`\n- **values.yaml** structure with defaults for:\n  - `redis.addr`, `redis.password`\n  - `router.replicas`, `router.image`, `router.service`, `router.resources`\n  - `workloadmanager.replicas`, `workloadmanager.image`, `workloadmanager.service`\n  - `volcano.scheduler.enabled` (optional)\n\n**Template files would be in:** `manifests/charts/base/templates/`\n- `workloadmanager.yaml` (Deployment + Service)\n- `agentcube-router.yaml` (Deployment + Service)\n- `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n- `rbac-router.yaml` (optional Role)\n- `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` (optional)\n- CRDs in `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n\n**Key RBAC Rules** defined for:\n- WorkloadManager ClusterRole (CRUD on sandboxes, sandboxclaims, codeinterpreters, etc.)\n- Router optional Role (secrets management)\n- Volcano scheduler ClusterRole\n\n---\n\n### 5. Manifests Module Structure\n\n**No dedicated \"manifests\" Go module found** in the `pkg/` directory. The Kubernetes manifests (Deployments, Services, RBAC, CRDs) are designed to be generated via the Helm chart but **the actual YAML files do not exist yet** - they're in the design/spec phase.\n\nThe relevant Go packages handle K8s operations:\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/` - Manages sandbox lifecycle\n- `pkg/router/` - Session-aware HTTP proxy\n- `pkg/store/` - Redis/Valkey persistence\n- `pkg/agentd/` - Idle cleanup controller\n- `pkg/apis/` - CRD type definitions\n\n---\n\n### 6. AR (Architecture Records) / ADR Documents\n\n**AR Format:** The project uses \"AR\" (Architecture Record) instead of traditional ADR. There are **30 ARs** (AR-001 through AR-030) in the `changes/` directory.\n\nEach AR directory typically contains:\n- `delta-spec.md` - GIVEN/WHEN/THEN acceptance scenarios (mandatory)\n- `tasks.md` - Implementation task checklist\n- `design.md` - Detailed design (some ARs)\n- `proposal.md` - High-level proposal (root level only)\n\n**No explicit ADR format found** - the project uses a custom \"AR\" (Architecture Record) taxonomy with a stage-based workflow (ST-0 through ST-7).\n\n---\n\n### Key Files Referenced:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md` | Main proposal (AR-029) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/deployment/design.md` | Helm chart design |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/deployment/spec.md` | Deployment requirements |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/project.md` | Project context |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/go.mod` | Go module definition |\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_285d5d944ffe5F72D5t70TRdlK","model":{"modelID":"MiniMax-M2.5","providerID":"bailian-coding-plan"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project","time":{"start":1775871076024,"end":1775871208593}}}}
