{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775871288150,"sessionID":"ses_285d5f3a3ffeBQhx48Y79H3M06","part":{"id":"prt_d7a2cdfab001K2OW1ONYKYyWGX","messageID":"msg_d7a2ccb7e001Ag3qmwDXoONzR0","sessionID":"ses_285d5f3a3ffeBQhx48Y79H3M06","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_1d420b43599948cf8d391c7e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-030: Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the Helm Chart templates and values configuration for deploying AgentCube to Kubernetes, providing a reusable, configurable deployment mechanism for the Workload Manager, Router, optional Volcano scheduler, and associated RBAC resources.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nAgentCube requires a standardized deployment mechanism to Kubernetes clusters. Currently, the system lacks a formal Helm chart for production deployments. The deployment/design.md and deployment/spec.md documents define the expected chart structure, but the actual template files need implementation.\n\nThe Helm chart enables:\n- Reproducible deployments across environments\n- Configuration management via values.yaml\n- Namespace-scoped installations\n- Optional components (RBAC, Volcano scheduler)\n- CRD lifecycle management\n\n### Goal\n\nCreate a complete Helm 3 chart at `manifests/charts/base/` that:\n- Renders Workload Manager Deployment + Service\n- Renders Router Deployment + Service\n- Renders RBAC resources (ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, optional Role)\n- Optionally renders Volcano agent scheduler resources\n- Ships CRDs for AgentCube runtime custom resources\n- Provides comprehensive values.yaml for configuration\n\n### Value\n\n- **Standardization**: Follows Kubernetes community conventions\n- **Operational Efficiency**: Single command deployment with configurable parameters\n- **Flexibility**: Optional components and extensive customization via values\n- **Security**: Proper RBAC with minimal privileges\n- **Maintainability**: Template-driven, version-controlled deployments\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| Chart.yaml | `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` | Helm chart metadata (name: agentcube, version: 0.1.0) |\n| values.yaml | `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Default configuration values |\n| WorkloadManager templates | `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | Deployment + Service |\n| Router templates | `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Deployment + Service |\n| RBAC templates | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding |\n| RBAC templates | `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Optional Role + RoleBinding (conditional) |\n| Volcano scheduler templates | `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` | Optional scheduler resources |\n| CRD manifests | `manifests/charts/base/crds/` | agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh, codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh |\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n\n- Kubernetes cluster provisioning\n- Ingress configuration\n- Prometheus/Grafana monitoring stack\n- Redis deployment (external dependency)\n- Application-level secrets management beyond RBAC\n- Multi-cluster deployment strategies\n- Helm hook-based upgrade migrations\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n|------------|---------|--------|\n| Helm 3 | Chart rendering and installation | Required |\n| Kubernetes 1.19+ | API versions used | Required |\n| Redis | Session storage (external) | Required at runtime |\n| agent-sandbox CRDs | Sandbox CRD definitions | Required for WorkloadManager ClusterRole |\n\n### Upstream\n\n- `deployment/design.md` — Helm chart specification\n- `deployment/spec.md` — Deployment requirements\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` — CRD type definitions (source for generated CRDs)\n- `docker/Dockerfile` — Workload Manager image build\n- `docker/Dockerfile.router` — Router image build\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Operators** — Deploy AgentCube via Helm\n2. **CI/CD pipelines** — Automated deployments via `helm upgrade --install`\n3. **E2E tests** — Use Helm for test cluster setup\n4. **Documentation** — Reference Helm values for configuration\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| CRD version mismatch | High | Ship CRDs with chart; require controller-gen v0.17.2 |\n| RBAC permissions too broad | Medium | Follow least-privilege; document required permissions |\n| Template rendering errors | Medium | Include Helm linting in CI |\n| Upgrade path complexity | Low | Document migration steps; use Helm hooks if needed |\n| Image pull failures | Medium | Support imagePullSecrets in values |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Raw YAML manifests (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Simple, no templating dependency, version control friendly\n**Cons**: No parameterization, duplication across environments, harder to maintain, no Helm ecosystem integration\n\n### Option 2: Kustomize (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Native Kubernetes configuration management, overlays for environments\n**Cons**: Less widely adopted in operator tooling, Helm more common for single-command installs, additional learning curve\n\n### Option 3: Ansible/Kubectl (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Flexible, idempotent\n**Cons**: Additional tool dependency, less declarative, harder to version and rollback\n\n### Option 4: Helm 3 chart (Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Industry standard, extensive ecosystem, values parameterization, rollback support, Helm hooks for lifecycle\n**Cons**: Templating complexity, requires Helm knowledge\n\n---\n\n## Technical Design\n\n### Chart Structure\n\n```\nmanifests/charts/base/\n├── Chart.yaml\n├── values.yaml\n├── templates/\n│   ├── workloadmanager.yaml\n│   ├── agentcube-router.yaml\n│   ├── rbac/\n│   │   └── workloadmanager.yaml\n│   ├── rbac-router.yaml (conditional)\n│   └── volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml (conditional)\n└── crds/\n    ├── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml\n    └── runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml\n```\n\n### values.yaml Key Tree\n\n| Path | Type | Default |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n| `redis.addr` | string | `\"\"` (required) |\n| `redis.password` | string | `\"\"` |\n| `router.replicas` | int | `1` |\n| `router.image.*` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router:latest` |\n| `router.service.*` | object | ClusterIP:8080 |\n| `router.resources.*` | object | CPU/memory limits |\n| `router.rbac.create` | bool | `false` |\n| `workloadmanager.replicas` | int | `1` |\n| `workloadmanager.image.*` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager:latest` |\n| `workloadmanager.service.*` | object | ClusterIP:8080 |\n| `workloadmanager.resources.*` | object | CPU/memory limits |\n| `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | bool | `false` |\n\n### Template Logic\n\n#### WorkloadManager Deployment\n- Uses `workloadmanager.replicas` count\n- Sets `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` via downward API\n- Injects `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD` from values\n- Health probes: HTTP GET `/health`\n- Resource limits from values\n\n#### Router Deployment\n- Uses `router.replicas` count\n- Sets `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` = `http://workloadmanager.{{.Release.Namespace}}.svc.cluster.local:{{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n- Injects Redis env vars\n- Health probes: `/health/live`, `/health/ready`\n- Conditional RBAC based on `router.rbac.create`\n\n#### RBAC\n- ClusterRole `workloadmanager`: CRUD on sandboxes, sandboxclaims, codeinterpreters, agentruntimes, pods, secrets; tokenreviews\n- Optional Role `router`: secret management in namespace\n\n#### Volcano Scheduler (Conditional)\n- Rendered only when `volcano.scheduler.enabled: true`\n- Includes ServiceAccount, ConfigMap, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding, Service, Deployment\n\n### CRD Shipment\n\nCRDs installed via chart's `crds/` directory:\n- `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n- `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Chart scaffolding\n\n- [ ] Create `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml`\n- [ ] Create `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` with documented defaults\n- [ ] Create `manifests/charts/base/templates/.gitkeep`\n- [ ] Create `manifests/charts/base/crds/.gitkeep`\n\n### Phase 2: Core templates\n\n- [ ] Create `templates/workloadmanager.yaml` (Deployment + Service)\n- [ ] Create `templates/agentcube-router.yaml` (Deployment + Service)\n- [ ] Add health probe configurations\n- [ ] Add resource limits templating\n\n### Phase 3: RBAC templates\n\n- [ ] Create `templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n- [ ] Create `templates/rbac-router.yaml` (conditional Role + RoleBinding)\n- [ ] Define ClusterRole rules matching agent-sandbox and AgentCube CRDs\n\n### Phase 4: Optional components\n\n- [ ] Create `templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` (conditional)\n- [ ] Add ConfigMap with agent-scheduler.conf\n- [ ] Add Volcano ClusterRole rules\n\n### Phase 5: CRDs\n\n- [ ] Add CRD manifests to `crds/` directory\n- [ ] Verify CRD API group and version\n\n### Phase 6: Validation\n\n- [ ] Add Helm linting to Makefile\n- [ ] Test template rendering with `helm template`\n- [ ] Verify RBAC rule correctness\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| HELM-001 | Chart.yaml renders | Valid Helm chart with name=agentcube, version=0.1.0 |\n| HELM-002 | Default values.yaml | Contains all documented keys with correct defaults |\n| HELM-003 | WorkloadManager deployment | Deployment with replicas from values, correct image, env vars |\n| HELM-004 | WorkloadManager service | Service with correct port mapping |\n| HELM-005 | Router deployment | Deployment with WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL correctly constructed |\n| HELM-006 | Router service | Service with type from values |\n| HELM-007 | RBAC rendered | ServiceAccount + ClusterRole + ClusterRoleBinding present |\n| HELM-008 | Optional router RBAC | Role rendered only when router.rbac.create=true |\n| HELM-009 | Optional Volcano | Scheduler resources rendered only when enabled |\n| HELM-010 | CRDs present | Both agentruntime and codeinterpreter CRDs in crds/ |\n| HELM-011 | Helm lint passes | `helm lint manifests/charts/base` succeeds |\n| HELM-012 | Template dry-run | `helm template test manifests/charts/base` renders without error |\n\n---\n\n## Timeline Estimate\n\n| Phase | Effort |\n|-------|--------|\n| Chart scaffolding | 1 hour |\n| Core templates | 3 hours |\n| RBAC templates | 2 hours |\n| Optional components | 2 hours |\n| CRDs | 1 hour |\n| Validation & testing | 2 hours |\n| **Total** | **11 hours** |\n\n---\n\n## Relationship to Other ARs\n\nAR-030 provides the deployment mechanism for all AgentCube components:\n\n- AR-027, AR-028 — SDK clients depend on deployed services\n- AR-029 — HTTP client layer communicates with Workload Manager and Router\n- The Go binaries (workload-manager, router, agentd, picod) require this chart for Kubernetes deployment","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-030/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775871288138,"end":1775871288147}}}}
